  "tune": "Duke Street",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "When I survey the wondrous cross On which the Prince of Glory died, My richest gain I count but loss, And pour contempt on all my pride.",
    "v2": "Forbid it, Lord, that I should boast, Save in the death of Christ my God! All the vain things that charm me most, I sacrifice them to His blood.",
    "v3": "See from His head, His hands, His feet, Sorrow and love flow mingled down! Did e&#39;er such love and sorrow meet, Or thorns compose so rich a crown?",
    "v4": "His dying crimson, like a robe, Spreads o&#39;er His body on the tree; Then I am dead to all the globe, And all the globe is dead to me.",
    "v5": "Were the whole realm of nature mine, That were a present far too small; Love so amazing, so divine, Demands my soul, my life, my all."
  },
